New York City Mask Mandate for Toddlers is Already Back and Will Remain in Place

🇺🇸😷@COVID19Up: New York City's mask mandate for children ages 2-4 will remain in place. The city was granted a stay from an appeals court on Friday (April 1) evening. 

Masks will now be back, starting on Monday (April 4).

The ruling clears the way for the city's toddlers to return to school and other childcare settings Monday with masks on, after New York City Mayor Eric Adams said he would delay ending the mask mandate.

Earlier on Friday, Judge Ralph Porzio ruled that he found the mask mandate to be arbitrary, capricious and unreasonable after a group of parents accused the city of enacting unconstitutional mandates and sought to prevent the city from issuing new mandates without authorization from the state legislature.

"We are obviously disappointed. There was no reason the city needed to rush to the appellate division on a Friday afternoon just so a three year old could return to school in a mask," said Michael Cessa, an attorney for a group of parents who sued the city over the toddler mask mandate.

Email Testimony

From: Eric

PM,
I recently received the healing of my knee pain while listening to one of your interviews. I initially was drawn to that interview to gain an understanding of a current event that the title suggested would be discussed. I had appreciated your Q drop analysis over the past few years and value your insights from a God centered perspective. Part of that interview turned to your faith healing journey and the process that you had gone through to make it effective over time.
At that time I had been dealing with constant knee pain for about 8 months following a fun filled weekend of waverunner riding. Having been a martial artist for over a decade, an avid off-road motorcycle racer for ten years, and an all around adventure enthusiast all my life I was surprised to have sustained an injury from such a low impact activity. I figured that all the years of my athletic past had finally taken its toll.
You discribe how God has provided us all with the ability to heal ourselves and that we all had this ability to access this by acknowledging Gods power within ourselves and command ourselves to be healed. I repeated the prayer that you had advised commanding the power that God had given me to heal the knee pain I had been experiencing. Immediately I took a few steps to determine if the same level of pain was present. Those first steps were definitely different then all that I had taken in the prior 8 months. The next step was to try to squat in place which would have been impossible just minutes before. To my complete amazement and overwhelming joy I was able to squat in place for the first time in 8 months!
It has now been 2 months since that day and my knee pain has not returned. I give God all the credit and thank him daily for what I know is a miracle he has provided. I have relayed my testimony to everyone close to me especially those who had noticed the debilitating effects the pain had been causing.
Thank you David for bringing me closer to God and allowing those most important to me to witness an undeniable miracle.
